# Product Capabilities (v2)

**This version — one role:** `owner` on **both** personal and professional. Owner uses the system alone.

**Next version (not now):** `customer` (catalog / orders or trades). **Never in this phase:** `staff`, `guest`, `customer` signup or routes.

## Roles

| Role | Personal | Professional |
|------|:--------:|:------------:|
| `owner` | ✅ | ✅ |

`roles_enabled: [owner]` for all presets until customer release.

## Capabilities (owner only, now)

| Capability | Module |
|------------|--------|
| `manage_inventory` | `inventory` |
| `view_pricing` | `pricing_visibility` |
| `view_profit` | `profit_analytics` |
| `approve_orders` | `orders` (owner-managed; no customer checkout yet) |
| `place_orders` | — **defer** with `customer` role |

`resolve_capabilities()` in `core/capabilities.py`; `require_capability(...)`.

**Presets:** personal → `[owner]`, orders off; professional → `[owner]`, orders/profit per module flags.

**403:** `module_disabled` | `capability_disabled` | `role_not_enabled` | `forbidden`
